":"1460","1360":"1360","1338":"1338","1468":"1468","1401":"1401","1500":"1500","1423":"1423","1357":"1357","1400":"1400","1442":"1442","1365":"1365","about 1365":"about 1365","1408":"1408","about 1384":"about 1384","of Rhydlafar,St Fagan's,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Saint Fagans, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","of Saint Mellons, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Saint Mellons, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Dyffryn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Radyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom":"Radyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kemeys","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Keys  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Keys","meanings":["English, Irish and Scottish: variant of   Keyes  ."]}]},{"name":"Margred","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Margaret</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margred Kemeys was born about 1365, in Saint Mellons, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Jenkin Kemeys, was 28 and her mother, Crisli verch Morgan, was 28. She had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Ieuan Fychan. She died in 1401, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 37."},"et":{"about 1365–1401":"umbes 1365–1401","1360–1460":"1360–1460","1365–1401":"1365–1401","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1423–1500":"1423–1500","1384–Male":"1384–Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1442–1468":"1442–1468","1338–1408":"1338–1408","1338–Female":"1338–Surnud","ABT    1400":"umbes 1400","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1360":"1360","1338":"1338","1468":"1468","1401":"1401","1500":"1500","1423":"1423","1357":"1357","1400":"1400","1442":"1442","1365":"1365","about 1365":"umbes 1365","1408":"1408","about 1384":"umbes 1384","of Rhydlafar,St Fagan's,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Saint Fagans, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","of Saint Mellons, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Saint Mellons, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Dyffryn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Radyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom":"Radyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1365–1401":"noin 1365–1401","1360–1460":"1360–1460","1365–1401":"1365–1401","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1423–1500":"1423–1500","1384–Male":"1384–Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1442–1468":"1442–1468","1338–1408":"1338–1408","1338–Female":"1338–Kuollut","ABT    1400":"noin 1400","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1360":"1360","1338":"1338","1468":"1468","1401":"1401","1500":"1500","1423":"1423","1357":"1357","1400":"1400","1442":"1442","1365":"1365","about 1365":"noin 1365","1408":"1408","about 1384":"noin 1384","of Rhydlafar,St Fagan's,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Saint